	     superBT V04 -- super TC Best Track 1st beta version
				 Mike Fiorino
			       mfiorino@gmu.edu
				   20240110

0. Intro:
--------

This tarball contains the first beta version of the superBT (04) -- a tropical
cyclone (TC) Best Track data set -- a superposition/merging/combination of:

1) all TC position/structure operational data from JTWC/NHC (i.e., is more than the
'best track' or ATCF 'bdeck' data available in IBTRaCS)

2) TC storm and environmental diagnostic variables from the latest/greatest
ECMWF reanlysis ERA5 (dynamics)

3) TC rain from three high-resolution satellite-precipitation analyses:
CMORPH, GsMAP and IMERG (theromdynamics)

1. Contents:
-----------

README				# this files
README-sbt-mike5		# technical information on the development platform (mike5)
README-sbt-py2			# doc on the python2 interface
README-sbt-vars			# variable description from the three meta data files

data files:

superBT/V04/all-md3-2007-2022-MRG.csv     # all md3 position/structure for each TC
superBT/V04/sum-md3-2007-2022-MRG.csv     # summary of each TC
superBT/V04/sbt-v04-2007-2022-MRG.csv	  # superBT for each unique position in all-md3

meta data files:

superBT/V04/h-meta-md3-vars.csv
superBT/V04/h-meta-md3-sum.csv
superBT/V04/h-meta-sbt-v04-vars.csv


py2 files with variables/methods/classes:
    
superBT/V04/py2/mf.py			  # original .py from 1999 with NWP variables/methods
superBT/V04/py2/sBTcl.py		  # classes
superBT/V04/py2/sbtLocal.py		  # local file that must contain full path to superBT/V04/ dir
superBT/V04/py2/sBT.py			  # imports mf,sBTvars,sBTvars,sBTvm
superBT/V04/py2/sBTvars.py		  # variables
superBT/V04/py2/sBTvm.py		  # variables and methods

py2 applications to list/analyze and plot md3 and sbt data -- see README-sbt-py2 for details

superBT/V04/py2/p-md3-ls.py	     	  # mdeck3 (md3) listing of storms and posits/structure
superBT/V04/py2/p-md3-stm-anl.py	  # analyze formation rate (9x -> NN)
superBT/V04/py2/p-sbt-v04-anl-ts.py	  # analyze difference between 9Xdev and 9Xnon
superBT/V04/py2/p-sbt-v04-anl-var.py	  # list/make .csv of sbt and md3 variables


2. Data Files:
-------------

The superBT-V04 consists of three .csv text data files:

all-md3-2007-2022-MRG.csv -- the mdeck3 TC position/strucure data
sum-md3-2007-2022-MRG.csv -- one-line summary of each TC in all-md3-2007-2022-MRG.csv
sbt-v04-2007-2022-MRG.csv -- the superBT with diagnostics and precipitation
			     for each TC in the mdeck3 file

each variable in the three .csv is described in the associated meta data
files:

h-meta-md3-vars.csv      -- variables in the mdeck3 TC position/structure data
h-meta-md3-sum.csv       -- summary of mdeck3 by storm
h-meta-sbt-v04-vars.csv  -- variables in the superBT

